It's time to apply your ceramic Material to your weapons so they look ceramic instead of metallic.

## Steps

[EXCERPT:NewPistol]

1. Double-click one of your weapon Blueprints in the Content Browser to edit it in the [Blueprint Editor](Engine/Blueprints/Editor).

	![](weapon_edit.png)

1. Select the **WeapMesh** Component in the Components panel.

	![](mesh_select.png)

1. Back in the Content Browser, select the _Mat_Ceramic_ Material.

1. In the Details panel, find the **Materials** category and click the **Use Selected Asset from Content BRowser** button to apply the _Mat_Ceramic_ Material to the weapon mesh.

	![](mat_assign.png)

1. Click the **Compile** button in the Blueprint Editor toolbar to update the Blueprint with the changes.

	![](weapon_compile.png)

1. Click the **Save** button in the Blueprint Editor toolbar to save the weapon asset.

	![](weapon_save.png)

1. Repeat these steps for the other weapon Blueprints in your mod to make them all ceramic.

[/EXCERPT]

## Result

The Preview panel shows the ceramic weapon. In the next step, you will test out the mod to see your ceramic weapons in action!

![](weapon_ceramic.png)

